components.name: Extract Ensembl Mapping Files
components.description: Checks Ensembl FTP for new genomic mapping TSV.GZ files and downloads any new versions to the S3 raw landing zone.
outputs: new genomic mapping files in S3 raw landing zone (s3://cqgc-{env}-app-datalake/raw/landing/ensembl/)

components.name: Transform Ensembl Mapping with Spark
components.description: Runs a Spark job on Kubernetes to read the raw Ensembl files from S3, process them, and write structured mapping tables back to the data lake.
inputs: raw Ensembl mapping files in S3 landing zone (s3://cqgc-{env}-app-datalake/raw/landing/ensembl/)
outputs: processed Ensembl mapping tables in the data lake (e.g., parquet or Delta tables)

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful completion of extract_ensembl_files

connections.purpose: Read raw files and write processed tables

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

ftp_server_path.description: Ensembl FTP server path for genomic mapping files

mapping_types.description: List of mapping types to process (canonical, ena, entrez, refseq, uniprot)

s3_key_path.description: S3 key path for raw landing zone (raw/landing/ensembl/)

config_file.description: Configuration file for Spark job (e.g., config-etl-large)

table_name.description: Target table name for processed Ensembl mapping (ensembl_mapping)

steps.description: Processing steps identifier (default if not overridden)

k8s_context.description: Kubernetes execution context for Spark job (K8sContext.ETL)

sources: Ensembl FTP server providing genomic mapping TSV.GZ files (canonical, ena, entrez, refseq, uniprot)
sinks: Processed Ensembl mapping tables stored in the S3 data lake (e.g., s3://cqgc-{env}-app-datalake/processed/ensembl_mapping/)
